{
  "info": {
    "name": "NME - API v2 (JWT)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "nme-api-v2-jwt-v1",
    "description": "## Migrating the app from v1 to v2\n\nv2 is a parallel API for the new app — v1 (api/*) is untouched and keeps working exactly as before for the live app. Every v2 request/response field is identical to its v1 counterpart; only the URL and the auth mechanism change.\n\n**1. URL:** insert `v2/` after `api/` — e.g. `api/get_my_jobs` -> `api/v2/get_my_jobs`.\n\n**2. Login screen:** replaced entirely. v1 used username/password; v2 uses email + OTP:\n- New user -> `email_register_otp` (email). Returning user -> `email_login_otp` (email) — fails if the email isn't already registered.\n- User enters the 6-digit code they received -> `email_verify_otp` (email, otp). The response now includes a `token` field (JWT) alongside the existing `data` user object.\n\n**3. Stop relying on cookies.** v1 used a session cookie set automatically by the HTTP client. v2 has no cookies at all — save `token` from `email_verify_otp` into secure storage (Keychain / Keystore / equivalent).\n\n**4. Attach the token to every v2 request** (except the 3 email OTP endpoints and `get_business/{id}`, which is public on both versions):\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\nThis collection does it for you automatically via the Bearer auth configured at the collection level, driven by the `{{jwt_token}}` variable — which the Email Verify OTP request's Tests script auto-fills on a successful response.\n\n**5. Handle expiry (30 days).** There's no HTTP 401 — like the rest of this API, v2 always returns 200 with a JSON body. Watch for:\n```json\n{\"status\": 0, \"message\": \"Valid Authorization: Bearer <token> required\"}\n```\nWhen you see that, clear the stored token and send the user back to the email-OTP login screen rather than retrying the request."
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      { "key": "token", "value": "{{jwt_token}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost/nme-api", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "jwt_token", "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Auto-filled by the Email Verify OTP request's Tests script on success." }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth (Email OTP)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Email Register OTP",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v2/email_register_otp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v2", "email_register_otp"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                { "key": "email", "value": "newuser@example.com", "type": "text", "description": "Required. Must NOT already belong to an existing user." }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Step 1 of registering a brand-new account. Sends a 6-digit OTP (valid 5 minutes) via the SMTP settings in the app_settings dashboard. Fails if the email is already registered — use Email Login OTP instead."
          },
          "response": [
            { "name": "OTP Sent", "status": "OK", "code": 200, "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }], "body": "{\n  \"status\": 1,\n  \"message\": \"OTP sent to email\"\n}" },
            { "name": "Email Already Registered", "status": "OK", "code": 200, "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }], "body": "{\n  \"status\": 0,\n  \"message\": \"Email already registered, please login\"\n}" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Email Login OTP",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v2/email_login_otp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v2", "email_login_otp"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                { "key": "email", "value": "existinguser@example.com", "type": "text", "description": "Required. Must belong to an existing user." }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Step 1 of logging into an existing account. Sends a 6-digit OTP (valid 5 minutes). Fails if the email is not registered — use Email Register OTP instead."
          },
          "response": [
            { "name": "OTP Sent", "status": "OK", "code": 200, "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }], "body": "{\n  \"status\": 1,\n  \"message\": \"OTP sent to email\"\n}" },
            { "name": "Email Not Registered", "status": "OK", "code": 200, "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }], "body": "{\n  \"status\": 0,\n  \"message\": \"Email not registered, please register\"\n}" }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Email Verify OTP",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.status === 1 && body.token) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('jwt_token', body.token);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v2/email_verify_otp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v2", "email_verify_otp"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                { "key": "email", "value": "newuser@example.com", "type": "text", "description": "Required. Same email used in the register/login OTP request." },
                { "key": "otp", "value": "123456", "type": "text", "description": "Required. The 6-digit code received by email." }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Step 2: verifies the OTP. On success, returns a JWT in the 'token' field — this request's Tests script auto-saves it into the {{jwt_token}} collection variable, so every other request in this collection (which inherits Bearer auth) works immediately after. Token is valid 30 days. Either creates the account (register flow) or logs into the existing one (login flow), depending on which OTP request preceded this call."
          },
          "response": [
            { "name": "Registration Successful", "status": "OK", "code": 200, "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }], "body": "{\n  \"status\": 1,\n  \"message\": \"Registration successful\",\n  \"data\": { \"id\": \"35\", \"email\": \"newuser@example.com\", \"...\": \"...\" },\n  \"token\": \"<JWT-issued-on-success-see-Tests-script>\"\n}" },
            { "name": "Login Successful", "status": "OK", "code": 200, "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }], "body": "{\n  \"status\": 1,\n  \"message\": \"Login successful\",\n  \"data\": { \"id\": \"35\", \"email\": \"existinguser@example.com\", \"...\": \"...\" },\n  \"token\": \"<JWT-issued-on-success-see-Tests-script>\"\n}" },
            { "name": "Invalid OTP", "status": "OK", "code": 200, "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }], "body": "{\n  \"status\": 0,\n  \"message\": \"Invalid OTP\"\n}" },
            { "name": "OTP Expired", "status": "OK", "code": 200, "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }], "body": "{\n  \"status\": 0,\n  \"message\": \"OTP expired, please request a new one\"\n}" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
